  3,2,"God! There is no god ňĻworthy of worshipňļ except Him‚ÄĒthe Ever-Living, All-Sustaining"
  3,3,"He has revealed to you ňĻO Prophetňļ the Book in truth, confirming what came before it, as He revealed the Torah and the Gospel"
  3,4,"previously, as a guide for people, and ňĻalsoňļ revealed the Standard ňĻto distinguish between right and wrongňļ.¬†Surely those who reject God‚Äôs revelations will suffer a severe torment. For God is Almighty, capable of punishment"
  3,5,Surely nothing on earth or in the heavens is hidden from God
  3,6,"He is the One Who shapes you in the wombs of your mothers as He wills. There is no god ňĻworthy of worshipňļ except Him‚ÄĒthe Almighty, All-Wise"
  3,7,"He is the One Who has revealed to you ňĻO Prophetňļ the Book, of which some verses are precise‚ÄĒthey are the foundation of the Book‚ÄĒwhile others are elusive.¬†Those with deviant hearts follow the elusive verses seeking ňĻto spreadňļ doubt through their ňĻfalseňļ interpretations‚ÄĒbut none grasps their ňĻfullňļ meaning except God. As for those well-grounded in knowledge, they say, ‚ÄúWe believe in this ňĻQuranňļ‚ÄĒit is all from our Lord.‚ÄĚ But none will be mindful ňĻof thisňļ except people of reason"
  3,8,"ňĻThey say,ňļ ‚ÄúOur Lord! Do not let our hearts deviate after you have guided us. Grant us Your mercy. You are indeed the Giver ňĻof all bountiesňļ"
  3,9,Our Lord! You will certainly gather all humanity for the ňĻpromisedňļ Day‚ÄĒabout which there is no doubt. Surely God does not break His promise.‚ÄĚ
  3,10,"Indeed, neither the wealth nor children¬†of the disbelievers will be of any benefit to them against God‚ÄĒand they will be the fuel for the Fire"
  3,11,"Their fate will be like that of the people of Pharaoh and those before them‚ÄĒthey all rejected Our signs, so God seized them for their sins. And God is severe in punishment"
  3,12,"ňĻO Prophet!ňļ Tell the disbelievers, ‚ÄúSoon you will be overpowered and driven to Hell‚ÄĒwhat an evil place to rest!‚ÄĚ"
  3,13,"Indeed, there was a sign for you in the two armies that met in battle‚ÄĒone fighting for the cause of God and the other in denial. The believers saw their enemy twice their number.¬†But God supports with His victory whoever He wills. Surely in this is a lesson for people of insight"
  3,14,"The enjoyment of ňĻworldlyňļ desires‚ÄĒwomen, children,¬†treasures of gold and silver, fine horses, cattle, and fertile land‚ÄĒhas been made appealing to people. These are the pleasures of this worldly life, but with God is the finest destination"
  3,15,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúShall I inform you of what is better than ňĻall ofňļ this? Those mindful ňĻof Godňļ will have Gardens with their Lord under which rivers flow, to stay there forever, and pure spouses,¬†along with God‚Äôs pleasure.‚ÄĚ And God is All-Seeing of ňĻHisňļ servants"
  3,16,"who pray, ‚ÄúOur Lord! We have believed, so forgive our sins and protect us from the torment of the Fire.‚ÄĚ"
  3,17,"ňĻIt is theyňļ who are patient, sincere, obedient, and charitable, and who pray for forgiveness before dawn"
  3,18,"God ňĻHimselfňļ is a Witness that there is no god ňĻworthy of worshipňļ except Him‚ÄĒand so are the angels and people of knowledge. He is the Maintainer of justice. There is no god ňĻworthy of worshipňļ except Him‚ÄĒthe Almighty, All-Wise"
  3,19,"Certainly, God‚Äôs only Way is Islam.¬†Those who were given the Scripture did not dispute ňĻamong themselvesňļ out of mutual envy until knowledge came to them.¬†Whoever denies God‚Äôs signs, then surely God is swift in reckoning"
  3,20,"So if they argue with you ňĻO Prophetňļ, say, ‚ÄúI have submitted myself to God, and so have my followers.‚ÄĚ And ask those who were given the Scripture and the illiterate ňĻpeopleňļ,¬†‚ÄúHave you submitted yourselves ňĻto Godňļ?‚ÄĚ If they submit, they will be ňĻrightlyňļ guided. But if they turn away, then your duty is only to deliver ňĻthe messageňļ. And God is All-Seeing of ňĻHisňļ servants"
  3,21,"Indeed, those who deny God‚Äôs signs, kill the prophets unjustly, and kill people who stand up for justice‚ÄĒgive them good news of a painful punishment"
  3,22,They are the ones whose deeds are wasted in this world and the Hereafter. And they will have no helpers
  3,23,"Have you not seen those who were given a portion of the Scriptures?¬†Yet when they are invited to the Book of God to settle their disputes, some of them turn away heedlessly"
  3,24,"This is because they say, ‚ÄúThe Fire will not touch us except for a few days.‚ÄĚ They have been deceived in their faith by their wishful lying"
  3,25,"But how ňĻhorribleňļ will it be when We gather them together on the Day about which there is no doubt‚ÄĒwhen every soul will be paid in full for what it has done, and none will be wronged"
  3,26,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúO God! Lord over all authorities! You give authority to whoever You please and remove it from who You please; You honour whoever You please and disgrace who You please‚ÄĒall good is in Your Hands. Surely You ňĻaloneňļ are Most Capable of everything"
  3,27,You cause the night to pass into the day and the day into the night. You bring forth the living from the dead and the dead from the living. And You provide for whoever You will without limit.‚ÄĚ
  3,28,Believers should not take disbelievers as guardians instead of the believers‚ÄĒand whoever does so will have nothing to hope for from God‚ÄĒunless it is a precaution against their tyranny. And God warns you about Himself. And to God is the final return
  3,29,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúWhether you conceal what is in your hearts or reveal it, it is known to God. For He knows whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth. And God is Most Capable of everything.‚ÄĚ"
  3,30,ňĻWatch forňļ the Day when every soul will be presented with whatever good it has done. And it will wish that its misdeeds were far off. And God warns you about Himself. And God is Ever Gracious to ňĻHisňļ servants
  3,31,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúIf you ňĻsincerelyňļ love God, then follow me; God will love you and forgive your sins. For God is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful.‚ÄĚ"
  3,32,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúObey God and His Messenger.‚ÄĚ If they still turn away, then truly God does not like the disbelievers"
  3,33,"Indeed, God chose Adam, Noah, the family of Abraham, and the family of ‚ÄôImr√Ęn above all people ňĻof their timeňļ"
  3,34,"They are descendants of one another. And God is All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  3,35,"ňĻRememberňļ when the wife of ‚ÄôImr√Ęn said, ‚ÄúMy Lord! I dedicate what is in my womb entirely to Your service,¬†so accept it from me. You ňĻaloneňļ are truly the All-Hearing, All-Knowing.‚ÄĚ"
  3,36,"When she delivered, she said, ‚ÄúMy Lord! I have given birth to a girl,‚ÄĚ‚ÄĒand God fully knew what she had delivered‚ÄĒ‚Äúand the male is not like the female.¬†I have named her Mary, and I seek Your protection for her and her offspring from Satan, the accursed.‚ÄĚ"
  3,37,"So her Lord accepted her graciously and blessed her with a pleasant upbringing‚ÄĒentrusting her to the care of Zachariah. Whenever Zachariah visited her in the sanctuary, he found her supplied with provisions. He exclaimed, ‚ÄúO Mary! Where did this come from?‚ÄĚ She replied, ‚ÄúIt is from God. Surely God provides for whoever He wills without limit.‚ÄĚ"
  3,38,"Then and there Zachariah prayed to his Lord, saying, ‚ÄúMy Lord! Grant me‚ÄĒby your grace‚ÄĒrighteous offspring. You are certainly the Hearer of ňĻallňļ prayers.‚ÄĚ"
  3,39,"So the angels called out to him while he stood praying in the sanctuary, ‚ÄúGod gives you good news of ňĻthe birth ofňļ John who will confirm the Word of God and will be a great leader, chaste, and a prophet among the righteous.‚ÄĚ"
  3,40,"Zachariah exclaimed, ‚ÄúMy Lord! How can I have a son when I am very old and my wife is barren?‚ÄĚ He replied, ‚ÄúSo will it be. God does what He wills.‚ÄĚ"
  3,41,"Zachariah said, ‚ÄúMy Lord! Grant me a sign.‚ÄĚ He said, ‚ÄúYour sign is that you will not ňĻbe able toňļ speak to people for three days except through gestures. Remember your Lord often and glorify ňĻHimňļ morning and evening.‚ÄĚ"
  3,42,"And ňĻrememberňļ when the angels said, ‚ÄúO Mary! Surely God has selected you, purified you, and chosen you over all women of the world"
  3,43,"O Mary! Be devout to your Lord, prostrate yourself ňĻin prayerňļ and bow along with those who bow down.‚ÄĚ"
  3,44,"This is news of the unseen that We reveal to you ňĻO Prophetňļ. You were not with them when they cast lots to decide who would be Mary‚Äôs guardian, nor were you there when they argued ňĻabout itňļ"
  3,45,"ňĻRememberňļ when the angels proclaimed, ‚ÄúO Mary! God gives you good news of a Word¬†from Him, his name will be the Messiah,¬†Jesus, son of Mary; honoured in this world and the Hereafter, and he will be one of those nearest ňĻto Godňļ"
  3,46,And he will speak to people in ňĻhisňļ infancy and adulthood and will be one of the righteous.‚ÄĚ
  3,47,"Mary wondered, ‚ÄúMy Lord! How can I have a child when no man has ever touched me?‚ÄĚ An angel replied, ‚ÄúSo will it be. God creates what He wills. When He decrees a matter, He simply tells it, ‚ÄėBe!‚Äô And it is"
  3,48,"And God will teach him writing and wisdom, the Torah and the Gospel"
  3,49,"and ňĻmake himňļ a messenger to the Children of Israel ňĻto proclaim,ňļ ‚ÄėI have come to you with a sign from your Lord: I will make for you a bird from clay, breathe into it, and it will become a ňĻrealňļ bird‚ÄĒby God‚Äôs Will. I will heal the blind and the leper and raise the dead to life‚ÄĒby God‚Äôs Will. And I will prophesize what you eat and store in your houses. Surely in this is a sign for you if you ňĻtrulyňļ believe"
  3,50,"And I will confirm the Torah revealed before me and legalize some of what had been forbidden to you. I have come to you with a sign from your Lord, so be mindful of God and obey me"
  3,51,Surely God is my Lord and your Lord. So worship Him ňĻaloneňļ. This is the Straight Path.‚Äô‚ÄĚ
  3,52,"When Jesus sensed disbelief from his people, he asked, ‚ÄúWho will stand up with me for God?‚ÄĚ The disciples replied, ‚ÄúWe will stand up for God. We believe in God, so bear witness that we have submitted.‚ÄĚ"
  3,53,"ňĻThey prayed to God,ňļ ‚ÄúOur Lord! We believe in Your revelations and follow the messenger, so count us among those who bear witness.‚ÄĚ"
  3,54,"And the disbelievers made a plan ňĻagainst Jesusňļ, but God also planned‚ÄĒand God is the best of planners"
  3,55,"ňĻRememberňļ when God said, ‚ÄúO Jesus! I will take you¬†and raise you up to Myself. I will deliver you from those who disbelieve, and elevate your followers above the disbelievers until the Day of Judgment. Then to Me you will ňĻallňļ return, and I will settle all your disputes"
  3,56,"As for those who disbelieve, I will subject them to a severe punishment in this life and the Hereafter, and they will have no helpers"
  3,57,"And as for those who believe and do good, they will be rewarded in full. And God does not like the wrongdoers.‚ÄĚ"
  3,58,We recite ňĻallňļ this to you ňĻO Prophetňļ as one of the signs¬†and ňĻasňļ a wise reminder
  3,59,"Indeed, the example of Jesus in the sight of God is like that of Adam. He created him from dust, then said to him, ‚ÄúBe!‚ÄĚ And he was"
  3,60,"This is the truth from your Lord, so do not be one of those who doubt"
  3,61,"Now, whoever disputes with you ňĻO Prophetňļ concerning Jesus after full knowledge has come to you, say, ‚ÄúCome! Let us gather our children and your children, our women and your women, ourselves and yourselves‚ÄĒthen let us sincerely invoke God‚Äôs curse upon the liars.‚ÄĚ"
  3,62,"Certainly, this is the true narrative, and there is no god ňĻworthy of worshipňļ except God. And indeed, God ňĻaloneňļ is the Almighty, All-Wise"
  3,63,"If they turn away, then surely God has ňĻperfectňļ knowledge of the corruptors"
  3,64,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúO People of the Book! Let us come to common terms: that we will worship none but God, associate none with Him, nor take one another as lords instead of God.‚ÄĚ But if they turn away, then say, ‚ÄúBear witness that we have submitted ňĻto God aloneňļ.‚ÄĚ"
  3,65,"O People of the Book! Why do you argue about Abraham, while the Torah and the Gospel were not revealed until long after him? Do you not understand"
  3,66,"Here you are! You disputed about what you have ňĻlittleňļ knowledge of,¬†but why do you now argue about what you have no knowledge of?¬†God knows and you do not know"
  3,67,Abraham was neither a Jew nor a Christian; he submitted in all uprightness¬†and was not a polytheist
  3,68,"Indeed, those who have the best claim to Abraham are his followers, this Prophet,¬†and the believers. And God is the Guardian of those who believe"
  3,69,"Some of the People of the Book wish to mislead you ňĻbelieversňļ. They mislead none but themselves, yet they fail to perceive it"
  3,70,O People of the Book! Why do you reject the signs of God while you bear witness ňĻto their truthňļ
  3,71,O People of the Book! Why do you mix the truth with falsehood and hide the truth knowingly
  3,72,"A group among the People of the Book said ňĻto one anotherňļ, ‚ÄúBelieve in what has been revealed to the believers in the morning and reject it in the evening, so they may abandon their faith"
  3,73,"And only believe those who follow your religion.‚ÄĚ Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúSurely, ňĻthe onlyňļ true guidance is God‚Äôs guidance.‚ÄĚ ňĻThey also said,ňļ ‚ÄúDo not believe that someone will receive ňĻrevealedňļ knowledge similar to yours or argue against you before your Lord.‚ÄĚ Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúIndeed, all bounty is in the Hands of God‚ÄĒHe grants it to whoever He wills. And God is All-Bountiful, All-Knowing.‚ÄĚ"
  3,74,He chooses whoever He wills to receive His mercy. And God is the Lord of infinite bounty
  3,75,"There are some among the People of the Book who, if entrusted with a stack of gold, will readily return it. Yet there are others who, if entrusted with a single coin, will not repay it unless you constantly demand it. This is because they say, ‚ÄúWe are not accountable for ňĻexploitingňļ the Gentiles.‚ÄĚ¬†And ňĻsoňļ they attribute lies to God knowingly"
  3,76,Absolutely! Those who honour their trusts and shun evil‚ÄĒsurely God loves those who are mindful ňĻof Himňļ
  3,77,"Indeed, those who trade God‚Äôs covenant and their oaths for a fleeting gain will have no share in the Hereafter. God will neither speak to them, nor look at them, nor purify them on the Day of Judgment. And they will suffer a painful punishment"
  3,78,"There are some among them who distort the Book with their tongues to make you think this ňĻdistortionňļ is from the Book‚ÄĒbut it is not what the Book says. They say, ‚ÄúIt is from God‚ÄĚ‚ÄĒbut it is not from God. And ňĻsoňļ they attribute lies to God knowingly"
  3,79,"It is not appropriate for someone who God has blessed with the Scripture, wisdom, and prophethood to say to people, ‚ÄúWorship me instead of God.‚ÄĚ Rather, he would say, ‚ÄúBe devoted to the worship of your Lord ňĻaloneňļ‚ÄĚ‚ÄĒin accordance with what these prophets read in the Scripture and what they taught"
  3,80,And he would never ask you to take angels and prophets as lords. Would he ask you to disbelieve after you have submitted
  3,81,"ňĻRememberňļ when God made a covenant with the prophets, ňĻsaying,ňļ ‚ÄúNow that I have given you the Book and wisdom, if there comes to you a messenger¬†confirming what you have, you must believe in him and support him.‚ÄĚ He added, ‚ÄúDo you affirm this covenant and accept this commitment?‚ÄĚ They said, ‚ÄúYes, we do.‚ÄĚ God said, ‚ÄúThen bear witness, and I too am a Witness.‚ÄĚ"
  3,82,"Whoever turns back after this, they will be the rebellious"
  3,83,"Do they desire a way other than God‚Äôs‚ÄĒknowing that all those in the heavens and the earth submit to His Will, willingly or unwillingly, and to Him they will ňĻallňļ be returned"
  3,84,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúWe believe in God and what has been revealed to us and what was revealed to Abraham, Ishmael, Isaac, Jacob, and his descendants; and what was given to Moses, Jesus, and other prophets from their Lord‚ÄĒwe make no distinction between any of them, and to Him we ňĻfullyňļ submit.‚ÄĚ"
  3,85,"Whoever seeks a way other than Islam,¬†it will never be accepted from them, and in the Hereafter they will be among the losers"
  3,86,"How will God guide a people who chose to disbelieve after they had believed, acknowledged the Messenger to be true, and received clear proofs? For God does not guide the wrongdoing people"
  3,87,"Their reward is that they will be condemned by God, the angels, and all of humanity"
  3,88,"They will be in Hell forever. Their punishment will not be lightened, nor will they be delayed ňĻfrom itňļ"
  3,89,"As for those who repent afterwards and mend their ways, then surely God is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  3,90,"Indeed, those who disbelieve after having believed then increase in disbelief, their repentance will never be accepted.¬†It is they who are astray"
  3,91,"Indeed, if each of those who disbelieve then die as disbelievers were to offer a ransom of enough gold to fill the whole world, it would never be accepted from them. It is they who will suffer a painful punishment, and they will have no helpers"
  3,92,You will never achieve righteousness until you donate some of what you cherish. And whatever you give is certainly well known to God